qas.question: Which medieval town is on the UNESCO World Heritage List?
When were the preserved hill forts in Estonia built?
What institutional structures still exist from medieval times?

context: The architectural history of Estonia mainly reflects its contemporary development in northern Europe. Worth mentioning is especially the architectural ensemble that makes out the medieval old town of <a0_0>Tallinn<a0_0/>, which is on the UNESCO World Heritage List. In addition, the country has several unique, more or less preserved hill forts dating from <a1_0>pre-Christian times<a1_0/>, a large number of still intact medieval <a2_0>castles and churches<a2_0/>, while the countryside is still shaped by the presence of a vast number of manor houses from earlier centuries.
